Build bookworm-gnome sdcard for raspberrypi4b:

Input files: ../rootfs-bookworm/linaro-esp.img
             ../rootfs-bookworm/linaro-rootfs.img

cd ~/Downloads
wget https://github.com/pftf/RPi4/releases/download/v1.42/RPi4_UEFI_Firmware_v1.42.zip

cd ~/build-raspberrypi4b/bookworm-gnome

Plugin sdcard/USB2-SATA-SSD to PC.
sudo ./mksdcardimg.sh
sudo mount /dev/sda1 /mnt
cd /mnt
sudo 7z x ~/Downloads/RPi4_UEFI_Firmware_v1.42.zip
cd ~/build-raspberrypi4b/bookworm-gnome
sync
sudo umount /mnt
Eject sdcard/USB2 SATA ssd from PC.

Plugin sdcard/USB2-SATA-SSD to rpi4b.
Esc -> Device Manager -> Rpi -> Advanced -> 3GB ( disable ) -> F10 -> Boot Manager -> first UEFI or SDCARD.
Login:
Username: linaro
Password: linaro
Setup wifi. Disable power saving and screen saver.
uname -a
lsb_release -a
sudo ifconfig
sudo dpkg-reconfigure tzdata
sudo dpkg-reconfigure locales
date
sudo apt update
sudo apt upgrade
sync
free
sudo shutdown -h now
Power off rpi4b. Power on rpi4b.
sudo cat /sys/devices/system/cpu/cpu0/cpufreq/scaling_cur_freq
glxinfo | grep OpenGL
date
Check if Debian is running UEFI mode:
ls /sys/firmware/efi
Check display mode: ( wayland or x11 )
echo $XDG_SESSION_TYPE
Check audio driver: ( pulseaudio or pipewire )
pactl info

sudo apt install speedtest-cli python3-pip python3-setuptools ffmpeg mpv glmark2-es2-wayland pandoc firefox-esr vlc vlc-plugin-video-output rfkill

speedtest-cli --secure

glmark2-es2-wayland

aplay -l
pavucontrol  ( select hdmi as default )

firefox -> youtube.com -> search YmDNhi07_Ho

git clone https://github.com/yt-dlp/yt-dlp.git
cd yt-dlp
make
cd ../
~/yt-dlp/yt-dlp -f 'bestvideo[ext=mp4][protocol=https]+bestaudio[ext=m4a][protocol=https]' 3qrKjywjo7Q -o swan.mp4 --postprocessor-args " -c:v h264_v4l2m2m -b:v 2M -c:a copy"
mpv --hwdec=v4l2m2m-copy --log-file=mpv.log swan.mp4
grep Using mpv.log
cvlc --gl=wgl --glconv=any swan.mp4

Plugin ASUS USB-BT500 bluetooth usb dongle to rpi4b.
sudo rfkill list
hciconfig hci1
hcitool dev
hciconfig -a
